objective:
This course 
-focuses mainly on error-correcting codes, and a bit of information theory;
-requires some mathematical sophistication (linear algebra, number theory, modern algebra, probability);
-is programming intensive (with 6 programming assignments in C/C++). MATLAB is also used.

Textbooks: 
Error Correction Coding: mathematical methods and algorithms by Todd K. Moon, Wiley-Interscience, 2005. （全華書局代理）
